@node "introduction" "Introduction"

 Poolman is a launcher program. It's easy to use but also very
 simple.

@endnode

@node "features" "Features"

  Poolman has some features:

     * Poolman supports the use of exchange,where you can quit,hide,show
      poolman.
     * Has built in preference editor where you can customize it to suit you.

@endnode


@node "install" "Installation"

How to install Poolman

      Very easy to install. Just copy poolman.exe file to wherever
      you want it and run it. You will then get up the preference window.
      And can then set it up as you want to.

      If you start poolman and the "loading...please wait" just flashes,then
      it's most probably a problem in the prefs file. Try deleting
      envarc:poolman.prefs,and check exchange if poolman is running. If so
      quit it. And restart poolman.

@endnode

@node "Limitations" "Limitations"

Limitations of Poolman:

      *Supports only brushes at max 16 colours.
      *No anim support


@endnode
