@node "bug reports" "Known Bugs"

 I know there are a lot of bugs around. Here are some that I
 am aware of:

      * Add and delete buttons on the prefs does not work.
      * Get's wrong size of the brush,so the window does not
        match the brush size,usually the window is much bigger than the
        brush.

@endnode

@node "History" "Poolman History"
V0.5

     -Removed the x,y position buttons,found out that it was better with
      only one button for both x and y positions. Easier that way.

     -Added display of workbech font size in computer info. I had allready
      done the code,just forgot to use it.

     -Did some rework of the appearance of the prefs window,so it hopefully
      looks better and cleaner.

     -Reworked the exchange commodity output for poolman.

     -Fixed the position of the "can't find prefs" so should be displayed
      correctly now.

     -If you open the asl requester the text on the top would say that you
      can choose a brush file even if you are opening the file requester but
      is now fixed. Just a silly bug though.

     -Removed the version number at the top of the prefs window since it
      follows the number of the main program. It's considered as one
      program.

     -Found out that I loaded the brush palette twice,has now been fixed

     -Have fixed the problem with the window beeing twice the size of the
       brush. Seemed that I added the height of the brushes. :) 

     -Cleaned ut the code,removed not needed code i had incase something
      wasn't right. 

V0.4b

     -First version I let anyone test infact,but never released. Was to
      buggy and not really usable at all to be released.

@endnode

